Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows mildly elevated HbA1c, indicating prediabetes or suboptimal glycemic control. HDL cholesterol is low, which increases cardiovascular risk. Total CO₂ is slightly decreased, possibly reflecting mild metabolic acidosis or compensation. Other parameters, including renal function, electrolytes, and lipid profile, are within normal limits. Recommend further evaluation of glycemic control and cardiovascular risk management.
